  "intent_precise": "Twist Library Prep || Part 2: Ligate Adapters: Using pcr_plate (pcr_plate, slot 1), rsvr (labware, slot 4), Twist Universal Adapter Plate (pcr_plate, slot 2), mm_labware (labware, slot 7). With cold_mod module, mag_version module. (1) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (2) Pause: Please replace tips (3) Transfer from source to destination. (4) Mix mix_times times. (5) Transfer from source (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (6) Pause: msg1 (7) Transfer 80\u00b5L from source to destination. (8) Mix 10 times at 170\u00b5L. (9) Incubate for 5 minutes. (10) Engage magnets for bead separation. (11) Incubate for 1 minutes. (12) Transfer 180\u00b5L from source to destination. (13) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (14) Incubate for 1 minutes. (15) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (16) Incubate for 5 minutes. (17) Disengage magnets to release beads. (18) Transfer 17\u00b5L from source to destination. (19) Mix 5 times at 15\u00b5L. (20) Incubate for 2 minutes. (21) Engage magnets for bead separation. (22) Incubate for 3 minutes. (23) Transfer 15\u00b5L from source to destination.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (4\u00b0C). (volumes 15\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~18 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Twist Library Prep adapter ligation step, you'll need to set up your cold module at 4\u00b0C and have your PCR plate in slot 1, the Twist Universal Adapter Plate in slot 2, reservoir in slot 4, and master mix labware in slot 7. Start by replacing the tips, then transfer and mix your samples before adding 80\u00b5L and mixing 10 times at 170\u00b5L volume, followed by a 5-minute incubation. Engage the magnets for 1 minute, then perform your wash steps by transferring 180\u00b5L and 200\u00b5L volumes with 1-minute and 5-minute incubations respectively. Finally, disengage the magnets, add 17\u00b5L of your final reagent, mix 5 times at 15\u00b5L, incubate for 2 minutes, then re-engage magnets for 3 minutes before transferring the final 15\u00b5L.",
